{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos203.erdos_203 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos203.erdos_203.","id":"vf_077fed0558e990e2","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"OBLIGATION (Erdos #203). BANKED: a partial CRT covering certificate (m + 20 prime rows, ~0.7467 density) verified (crt_partial_cover). OPEN: extend to a full cover (the verified rows do not cover all residues).","id":"vf_0d4ac181db98ceaa","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #203: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Is there an integer $m$ with $(m,6)=1$ such that none of $2^k3^\\ell m+1$ are prime, for any $k,\\ell\\geq 0$? Prize: no. Tags: covering systems, primes.","id":"vf_c7746c4a8abee9ea","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[{"accepted":false,"banked":true,"claim":"Erdős #203 (is there m with (m,6)=1, no 2^k 3^l m+1 prime?): VERIFIED PARTIAL CRT cover + strategic reframing, Opus-verified. With m=8168305011630835886634520238999 (gcd(m,6)=1), 20 primes each kill an affine congruence class: p | 2^k3^l m+1 iff 2^k3^l == -m^{-1} mod p, ONE linear congruence alpha*k+beta*l == gamma mod h (h=lcm(ord_p2,ord_p3)=|<2,3> in F_p*|), NOT a single rectangle. All 20 rows independently verified (ord_p2/ord_p3/h, m mod p, T_p=-m^{-1}, and congruence <=> divisibility, 0 mismatches over all (k,l) mod h^2). Union kills density 87702779/117448695 ~= 0.7467 of the (k,l) lattice (Monte-Carlo-confirmed ~0.7468); surviving ~0.2533. This is a PARTIAL cover (NOT 100%), explicitly NOT a covering certificate and NOT a settlement of #203. Reframing: the 'one rectangle per prime' model is too weak (sum 1/(ord2 ord3) over p<=1e6 ~ 0.238 < 1); the quadratic-form/Iwaniec route applies to the q_i==1 mod 4 VARIANT (sum-of-two-squares), not the 2^k3^l semigroup; the '>=10^10' bound is heuristic not proven; Filaseta-Finch-Kozek argue 'finite covering or nothing' is too narrow. Verifi